or auoyded. Agesilaus being demanded of one how hee might purchase great fame, If thou contemnest▪ death (sayd he.) He whose spirit is seazed on with the feare of death; will neuer performe any memorable thing in war this passion will benumme &amp; withdraw mens hands from the goodliest exployts in the world. Plut. in Lacon. Alexander said that there was not any place so strong by nature or by art, that was safe for cowards. We reade that Philip king of Macedon hauing ma
