Then comes the sight so piercing and passionate after the faire faces of women, and stayes not there onely, but (O shamefull sight) it will see the bodies naked, the which is condemned both by God and man: Romulus condemned that man to death which suffered himselfe to bee seene naked by a woman; how much more is that woman to bee condemned, which layes aside all modestie with her smocke, as Giges said in Herodotus? The Emperours Lib. 1. 
