seemes subtill, but to speake truly it hath but the shew &amp; not the effect, for it is subiect to many pertinent answeres: First to alledge an inconuenience is not to dissolue the question. 2. It is a consequence ill applied, to say Such a one hath not spoken, therefore hee is no man.
                  Wee haue digged verie deepe into the earth, and yet wee neuer heard any of them that goe with their feete against ours; therefore there are no Antipodes; So the soules speake not vpon dead mens lippes, therefore they haue none: for beeing thus hindred, is the cause they neither heare nor see any signe of their life.
                  Thirdly, the teares of the dead mans kinsfolkes are ill

